channel.title: Money Making Methods
channel.description:
[b][u]This is a serious topic. Anyone spamming will be moderated without warning.[/u][/b]
Well everyone needs to know how to make money.
[b][u]Skilling Methods:[/u][/b] [b]Woodcutting:[/b] Once you get to level 60 woodcutting (65-70 is much better) you are able to cut yews. Yews sell for roughly 500 gp each, and sell almost instantly. I do not advise cutting magics at all, they are extremely slow (even compared to yews) and are only twice as much.
[b]Mining:[/b] You can mine iron at 15, and coal at 30. Both are pretty good money making levels.
[b]Fishing:[/b] At level 45 you catch lobsters.
[b]Runecrafting:[/b] At level 45 you can craft nature runes. Nature runes are used in quite a few popular spells, so the demand for them is pretty high.
[b]Hunter:[/b] At level 63 you can hunt red chinchompas. These currently sell for roughly 618 each, and they are what most people hunt to get 99. (47,796 are needed at 618 each, which is 29,537,928gp). Hunter is also a fast skill to train.
[b]Farming Herbs:[/b] Ranarr and snapdragon are the best, and can be farmed starting at level 32.
[b]Fletching/Alching Yew Long:[/b] For this to work, you have to do one of the following manually: Cut the logs, spin the flax, or get the Nature Runes. Whichever you choose you can buy the rest. You make profit and get great experience, which can be for fletching and magic, and either crafting, woodcutting, or runecrafting. (Thanks Lin). [b]Buy flax and spin it (Unless prices changed)[/b] (Thanks Lin)
[b][u]Combat Methods:[/u][/b] Kill Green Dragons sell both bones and hide. Last time I checked it's about 4K per dragon. (Thanks Lin)
[b][u]Other Methods:[/u][/b] Note: The following method is great, but be sure you are the only person doing it! I HIGHLY recommend 67 agility! Start off by buying a bunch of Faladar Teletabs, an anti-dragon shield, energy potions, and anything to reduce weight. Go to Falador with only 1-3 energy potions (3 if you don't have 67 agility) and your teletabs. Equip your weight-reducing stuff and anti-dragon shield and head to the Taverly Dungeon. If you have 67 agility, climb through the pipe to blue dragons. If not, run around. ALWAYS make sure run is on, and when you get low, drink your energy potions. Start collecting blue dragon scales. As soon as your inventory is full, teleport to Falador, bank the scales, restock on energy potions, and repeat. Once you're finished, grind the scales into dust (Unless scales sell for more. It's been a while), and then sell them. If I remember right, they sell for 600gp each. (Thanks Lin [size=1pt]little prick noticed that I forgot to mention him on this one[/size])
There are many more methods, feel free to post ones you have and I will be happy to add them here.
